<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1420,1886]" box="[264,366,1420,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1420,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1420,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[449,594,1460,1485]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Acanthaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,594,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Acanthaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was created by Sakai &amp; de 
<bibRefCitation box="[953,1206,1460,1486]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. &amp; de Saint Laurent, M. (1989) A check list of Axiidae (Decapoda, Crustacea, Thalassinidea, Anomura), with remarks and in addition descriptions of one new subfamily, eleven new genera and two new species. Naturalists, 3, 1 - 104." type="journal article">
Saint Laurent (
<number box="[1137,1198,1460,1486]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for eight species with 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 1987" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1987" box="[428,954,1500,1526]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilocheira" subGenus="Axiopsis">
<emphasis box="[428,528,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Axiopsis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[551,650,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Axiopsis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[674,795,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">pilocheira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" box="[808,954,1500,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. (1987) Two new Thalassinidea (Crustacea: Decapoda) from Japan, with the biogeographical distribution of the Japanese Thalassinidea. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41 (2), 396 - 308." type="journal article" year="1987">
Sakai, 
<number box="[895,954,1500,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1005,1056,1500,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
species. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. (1994) Eleven species of Australian Axiidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thalassinidea) with description of one new genus and five new species. The Beagle, 11, 175 - 202." type="journal article" year="1994">
Sakai (
<number box="[272,333,1540,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
increased, with 
<taxonomicName box="[550,726,1540,1565]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polycheates">
<emphasis box="[550,726,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. polycheates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the number of species to nine. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[1137,1323,1540,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Kensley, B. (1996) A new species of the axiid shrimp genus Acanthaxius from the Caribbean (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thalassinidea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 109 (1), 70 - 74." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kensley (
<number box="[1254,1315,1540,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered that “ 
<emphasis box="[463,1110,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">the definition of this genus contains some uncertainties</emphasis>
”, redefined it and limited the number of species to five: 
<taxonomicName authority="Yokoya, 1933" authorityName="Yokoya" authorityYear="1933" box="[736,1132,1620,1646]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miyazakiensis">
<emphasis box="[736,936,1620,1645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. miyazakiensis</emphasis>
(Yokoya, 
<number box="[1064,1124,1620,1646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1933.0">1933</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1282,1620,1646]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Miyake &amp; Sakai, 1967" authorityName="Miyake &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="1967" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amakusana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. amakusana</emphasis>
(Miyake &amp; Sakai, 
<number box="[621,681,1660,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Miyake &amp; Sakai, 1967" authorityName="Miyake &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="1967" box="[746,1214,1660,1686]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Acanthaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyacantha">
<emphasis box="[746,924,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. polyacantha</emphasis>
(Miyake &amp; Sakai, 
<number box="[1146,1206,1660,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the East 
<collectingCountry box="[323,393,1700,1726]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">China</collectingCountry>
Sea, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 1987" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1987" box="[460,780,1700,1726]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilocheira">
<emphasis box="[460,613,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. pilocheira</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" box="[630,772,1700,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. (1987) Two new Thalassinidea (Crustacea: Decapoda) from Japan, with the biogeographical distribution of the Japanese Thalassinidea. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41 (2), 396 - 308." type="journal article" year="1987">
Sakai, 
<number box="[712,772,1700,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[854,924,1700,1726]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 1994" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1994" box="[937,1257,1700,1726]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polychaetes">
<emphasis box="[937,1109,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. polychaetes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" box="[1118,1257,1700,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. (1994) Eleven species of Australian Axiidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thalassinidea) with description of one new genus and five new species. The Beagle, 11, 175 - 202." type="journal article" year="1994">
Sakai, 
<number box="[1198,1257,1700,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Great Barrier Reef, 
<collectingCountry box="[538,648,1740,1766]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Australia</collectingCountry>
, and added 
<taxonomicName authority="Kensley, 1996" authorityName="Kensley" authorityYear="1996" box="[785,1102,1740,1766]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirmilleri">
<emphasis box="[785,928,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. kirmilleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[935,1102,1740,1766]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Kensley, B. (1996) A new species of the axiid shrimp genus Acanthaxius from the Caribbean (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thalassinidea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 109 (1), 70 - 74." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kensley, 
<number box="[1043,1102,1740,1766]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from off 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1318,1740,1766]" name="Anguilla" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Anguilla</collectingCountry>
. Two other species were established in 
<number box="[723,786,1780,1806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1998.0">1998</number>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Kensley &amp; Chan" authorityName="Kensley &amp; Chan" box="[800,1139,1780,1806]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosa">
<emphasis box="[800,931,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. formosa</emphasis>
Kensley &amp; Chan
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kensley &amp; Chan" authorityName="Kensley &amp; Chan" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[1199,1323,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">A. grandis</emphasis>
Kensley &amp; Chan
</taxonomicName>
, both from 
<collectingCountry box="[597,687,1820,1846]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1420,1886]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1325,284,950]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<bibRefCitation author="Ngoc-Ho" box="[312,512,1860,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Ngoc-Ho, N. (2005) Thalassinidea (Crustacea, Decapoda) from French Polynesia. Zoosystema, 27 (1), 47 - 83." type="journal article" year="2005">
Ngoc­Ho (
<number box="[439,503,1860,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, describing a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1906" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1906" box="[835,1256,1860,1886]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Axius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissimus">
<emphasis box="[835,1071,1860,1885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Axius spinosissimus</emphasis>
Rathbun, 
<number box="[1197,1256,1860,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[264,473,284,310]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
, agreed with 
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[641,826,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Kensley, B. (1996) A new species of the axiid shrimp genus Acanthaxius from the Caribbean (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thalassinidea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 109 (1), 70 - 74." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kensley (
<number box="[757,818,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
that although this species was placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[264,409,324,349]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Acanthaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,409,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Acanthaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Sakai &amp; de 
<bibRefCitation box="[599,850,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. &amp; de Saint Laurent, M. (1989) A check list of Axiidae (Decapoda, Crustacea, Thalassinidea, Anomura), with remarks and in addition descriptions of one new subfamily, eleven new genera and two new species. Naturalists, 3, 1 - 104." type="journal article">
Saint Laurent (
<number box="[778,841,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, it did not fit the generic definition and should logically be assigned to a new genus. Nevertheless, as it comprised only three specimens including the 
<typeStatus box="[576,682,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">holotype</typeStatus>
, all damaged, it seemed undesirable to establish a monotypic taxon on a material in such poor condition. The species was provisionally retained in 
<taxonomicName box="[396,541,484,509]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Acanthaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[396,541,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Acanthaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ngoc-Ho" box="[556,746,484,510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Ngoc-Ho, N. (2005) Thalassinidea (Crustacea, Decapoda) from French Polynesia. Zoosystema, 27 (1), 47 - 83." type="journal article" year="2005">
Ngoc­Ho, 
<number box="[682,746,484,510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1325,284,950]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kensley" box="[475,661,524,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Kensley, B. (1996) A new species of the axiid shrimp genus Acanthaxius from the Caribbean (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thalassinidea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 109 (1), 70 - 74." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kensley (
<number box="[589,652,524,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the advanced characters of the genus are the relatively slender and dentate rostrum, with its basal pair of spines in a supraorbital position; the form of the pereopod 
<number box="[530,545,604,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
chela, and especially that of the small pereopod 
<number box="[1141,1156,604,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
, with slender dentate fingers being 
<number box="[519,553,644,670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.5">1.5</number>
–2.0 times longer than the propodal palm; the presence of spines on the upper margins of the dactylus and propodus of the pereopod 
<number box="[1054,1069,684,710]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
chela; the absence of pleurobranchs; and the presence of epipods on pereopods 
<number box="[941,987,724,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1325,284,950]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
The new species studied agree well with this scheme except for the fingers of the pereopod 
<quantity box="[383,430,804,830]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[440,591,804,829]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Acanthaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gadaletae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[440,591,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">A. gadaletae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[600,669,804,830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[600,669,804,830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
being only about 
<number box="[890,978,804,830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.3</number>
longer than the palm. It can also be noted that all known 
<taxonomicName box="[616,761,844,869]" class="Malacostraca" family="Axiidae" genus="Acanthaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[616,761,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Acanthaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have a slender and incurved tip of the antennal article 
<number box="[459,476,884,910]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
, as pointed out by Sakai &amp; de 
<bibRefCitation box="[865,1120,884,910]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Sakai, K. &amp; de Saint Laurent, M. (1989) A check list of Axiidae (Decapoda, Crustacea, Thalassinidea, Anomura), with remarks and in addition descriptions of one new subfamily, eleven new genera and two new species. Naturalists, 3, 1 - 104." type="journal article">
Saint Laurent (
<number box="[1048,1111,884,910]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, which could be considered as diagnostic.
</paragraph>
